Due to the mostly high-pressure areas over the southern part of Europe, the northern parts could see a lot of low-pressure areas coming in from the Atlantic. This resulted in relative wet conditions in most parts of Scandinavia (figure 7). Also the southern Alps and northern Italy were wetter than normal caused by the stau effects along the mountain ridge.
<br><br>
