<h2>The weather in February 2019</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
February was a warm month in Europe, but anomalies decreased from the northeast to the southwest (Figure 8). The reason was that in the northeast both daily maximum and minimum temperatures contributed to the warmth, while in the southwest only maxima were much higher than normal, but minima were around normal or even below.
<br><br>
As mentioned above, much of Europe often was under high-pressure influence that month, but northeastern Europe was also affected by warm air flow from the subtropics on several days which was redirected around the high pressure area to the northeast - day and night, causing a rise of daily maxima and minima. In contrast, southwestern Europe was mainly under influence of the Azores High - warm and sunny in daytime, but cold in the nights.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/feb2019/Stateofclimate_Feb2019_tn_0_25deg_anom_monthlymeans_2019_1981-2010_v19_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tn_baselayers_overlay_2019-02-28T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/feb2019/Stateofclimate_Feb2019_tn_0_25deg_anom_monthlymeans_2019_1981-2010_v19_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tn_baselayers_overlay_2019-02-28T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<a href="../images/feb2019/Stateofclimate_Feb2019_tg_0_25deg_anom_monthlymeans_2019_1981-2010_v19_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tg_baselayers_overlay_2019-02-28T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/feb2019/Stateofclimate_Feb2019_tg_0_25deg_anom_monthlymeans_2019_1981-2010_v19_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tg_baselayers_overlay_2019-02-28T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<a href="../images/feb2019/Stateofclimate_Feb2019_tx_0_25deg_anom_monthlymeans_2019_1981-2010_v19_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tx_baselayers_overlay_2019-02-28T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/feb2019/Stateofclimate_Feb2019_tx_0_25deg_anom_monthlymeans_2019_1981-2010_v19_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tx_baselayers_overlay_2019-02-28T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
