<br><br>
<em>Figure 8: February 2019 minimum (left), average (middle), and maximum (right) temperature differences from reference period 1981-2010 (E-OBS)</em>
<br><br>
Daily maxima were exceptionally above average that month especially in Southwestern and Central Europe (Figure 9), especially in the last days of the month, showing again the outstanding high pressure situation. However, also minima in the northeast were exceptionally high, which means that also the warm airflow caused very unusual warmth in a winter month.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/feb2019/Stateofclimate_Feb2019_tn_0_25deg_2019_month_pct_box_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tn_box_baselayers_overlay_2019-02-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/feb2019/Stateofclimate_Feb2019_tn_0_25deg_2019_month_pct_box_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tn_box_baselayers_overlay_2019-02-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
